As of the census<ref name=census>{{cite web | title = U.S. Census website | url = https://www.census.gov | publisher = [[United States Census Bureau]] | accessdate = May 23, 2011}}</ref> of 2010, there were 160 people living in the CDP. There were 79 housing units. The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|racial makeup]] of the town was 92.5% White, 3.1% American Indian and Alaska Native, 3.1% from some other race, and 1.3% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 8.1% of the population.

